[[File:Arf-jedi.jpg|thumb|200px|Arthur Papadam in his own Jedi costume.]]
'''Arthur (Arfy) Papadam''' wrote the backstory of [[Bal'demnic/Legends|Bal'demnic]], and co-wrote the backstory of [[Leektar/Legends|Leektar]] appearing in the [[Databank (original)|Databank]], through the ''[[What's The Story?]]'' feature of [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]].

In 2018 Arfy wrote and directed a fan film / mockumentary called ''The Dackwaller Files'', which he submitted in the 2018 Star Wars Fan Awards, Long Video category. It was selected as a finalist for the Audience Choice award.<ref name="fanfilm">{{SW|url=star-wars-fan-awards/long-video-vote|text=2018 ''Star Wars'' Fan Awards: Long Video Vote}}</ref>

He played for the [[2014]] national Australian quidditch team, and invented wheelchair quidditch in [[2011]].<ref name="quid">{{WebCite|url=http://iqaquidditch.com/news/2014/03/global-games-team-australia-announced|text=Global Games Team Australia Announced|archivedate=20140322080256}}</ref>

Arthur is a graphic designer, and redesigned the website of [[Abel G. Peña]] in [[2009]].

Other fan projects include the creation of ''Star Wars Outsider'' magazine in [[2007]], being a former administrator at [[Wookieepedia]] (under alias {{Srlink|User:Azizlight|Azizlight}}), and costume making (see Jedi costume pictured right).

His alias is "Arf Maul" on [[StarWars.com]], and [http://boards.theforce.net/members/612474 arf_maul] on [[TheForce.net]].

